text.tspan: #5: Iron with vitamins or minerals or both
Favours iron supplementation with vitamins or minerals or both

Sample sizes adjusted for clustering using an ICC of 0.15 (used the same ICC as stated in author's assumption). Design effect applied to account for 24 and 30 school clusters in intervention and control groups, respectively.
Tau² calculated by DerSimonian and Laird method.
(C) Blinding of participants and personnel (performance bias): iron deficiency/anaemia; Hb; iron status/deficiency
(D) Blinding of outcome assessment (detection bias): iron deficiency/anaemia; Hb; iron status/deficiency
(E) Incomplete outcome data (attrition bias): iron deficiency/anaemia; Hb; iron status/deficiency
